# React Guidelines

## Functional Components

- Mark all functional components with `React.FC` interface
- Use functional components, avoid class-based components
- Keep components under 100 lines of code
- Split large components into smaller chunks

```typescript
const MyComponent: React.FC = () => (
  <div>Content</div>
);

interface IMyComponentProps {
  title: string;
}

const MyComponent: React.FC<IMyComponentProps> = ({ title }) => (
  <div>{title}</div>
);
```

## MobX Integration

- Wrap reactive components with `observer` from `mobx-react`
- Use `useViewController` hook to access controllers
- Add `makeAutoObservable(this)` in controller constructors

```typescript
import { observer } from "mobx-react";
import { useViewController } from "data/hooks";

export const MyPage: React.FC = observer(() => {
  const { data } = useViewController<IMyController>(Bindings.MyController);
  return <div>{data}</div>;
});
```

## Fragments

- Use `<Fragment>` instead of `<>` shortcut

```typescript
// Bad
<>{children}</>

// Good
<Fragment>{children}</Fragment>
```
